		<h2>Information Collection and Use</h2>
		<p>
			MyInko may request access to certain device features to provide its core
			functionality:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Camera</strong>: Used to capture photos or scan images required
				by the app.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Location (GPS)</strong>: Used to determine your location for map
				or service tracking features.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Storage</strong>: Used to save and retrieve files related to the
				app’s operation (e.g., images or logs).
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Notifications</strong>: Used to send service updates or
				reminders relevant to the app’s functionality.
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			All permissions are used only for their stated purposes and are not used
			to collect personal data without your consent. No personal information is
			shared or stored on external servers unless required for app
			functionality.
		</p>

		<h2>Log Data</h2>
		<p>
			Whenever you use MyInko, in case of an error in the app, data and
			information (through third-party products) may be collected on your device
			called Log Data. This may include your device name, operating system
			version, app configuration, time and date of use, and other statistics.
		</p>

